org.forgerock.openam.cts.monitoring.impl

Class CTSMonitoringStoreImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.forgerock.openam.cts.monitoring.impl.CTSMonitoringStoreImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CTSConnectionMonitoringStore, CTSOperationsMonitoringStore, CTSReaperMonitoringStore

    @Singleton
public class CTSMonitoringStoreImpl
extends Object
implements CTSOperationsMonitoringStore, CTSReaperMonitoringStore, CTSConnectionMonitoringStore
    An implementation of the CTSOperationsMonitoringStore that stores the CTS monitoring information in internal data structure based on the type of monitoring information being stored.
    Since:
    12.0.0

    • Method Detail

      • addTokenOperation

        public void addTokenOperation(Token token,
                              CTSOperation operation,
                              boolean success)
        Adds a Token operation into the monitoring store.
        The operation is mapped to the type of the token. The operations per configurable period and cumulative count will be updated for the token type and operation.
        Passing in null as the token will mean that the operation is not mapped to a particular token type, this is for operations such as delete and list as the type of token cannot be determined. The operations per configurable period and cumulative count will be updated for the operation.
        Specified by:
        addTokenOperation in interface CTSOperationsMonitoringStore
        Parameters:
        token - The Token the operation was performed on.
        operation - The operation performed.
        success - Whether the operation was successful or not.

      • getAverageOperationsPerPeriod

        public double getAverageOperationsPerPeriod(TokenType type,
                                            CTSOperation operation)
        Gets the average rate of operations made in a given period.
        Will return the number of the specified operation made on the specified type token in a given (configurable) period.
        Passing in null as the operation will mean that the method will return the number of the specified operation made on tokens, which the type cannot be determined, i.e. Delete and List operations.
        Specified by:
        getAverageOperationsPerPeriod in interface CTSOperationsMonitoringStore
        Parameters:
        type - The type of token to get the operation average rate for.
        operation - The operation to get the average rate for.
        Returns:
        The average number of operations made on the type token in a given period.

        Will return the total number of the specified operation made on the specified type of token since the server stared.

      • getOperationFailuresCumulativeCount

        public long getOperationFailuresCumulativeCount(CTSOperation operation)
        Gets the cumulative count of failures of this operation type since server startup.
        Note that failure counts are not distinguished by token type as in most failure cases this information is not available. Uses the TokenOperationsStore to return the cumulative failure count.
        Specified by:
        getOperationFailuresCumulativeCount in interface CTSOperationsMonitoringStore
        Parameters:
